# 🧁 KaviCakes – Customer Website

## Phase-Wise Implementation Plan

---

## 🟢 PHASE 0 – CUSTOMER WEB BASE SETUP

### 🎯 Goal

Prepare the customer-facing web application to consume existing backend APIs.

### Tasks

* Create React web application
* Configure:

  * Client-side routing
  * Global layout (Navbar, Footer)
  * Authentication context (JWT handling)
  * API service layer (Axios / Fetch)
  * Environment variables for backend base URL

### Deliverables

* React project skeleton
* Public routes:

  * Home
  * Login
  * Register
* Protected routes:

  * Cart
  * Orders
  * Profile

📌 *No business logic is implemented in this phase, as all rules are handled by the backend.*

---

## 🟢 PHASE 1 – AUTHENTICATION & CUSTOMER PROFILE

### 🎯 Goal

Allow customers to create accounts and manage personal profiles.

### Tasks

* Customer registration
* Customer login using JWT authentication
* Secure token storage
* Logout functionality
* Profile view:

  * Name
  * Email
  * Phone number

### Backend Interaction

* `/auth/register`
* `/auth/login`
* `/customers/profile`

📌 *Uses the same authentication system as admin, with role = CUSTOMER.*

---

## 🟢 PHASE 2 – HOME PAGE & CAKE BROWSING

### 🎯 Goal

Enable customers to discover and explore available cakes.

### Home Page Features

* Search cakes by name or category
* Browse by category
* Featured cakes (newly added)
* Best sellers (based on ratings and order count)
* Recent approved feedback
* Navigation to:

  * Custom orders
  * Bulk orders

### Tasks

* Fetch cakes and related data
* Implement filters and search
* Render cake cards
* Implement “Order Now” call-to-action

### Backend Interaction

* `/cakes`
* `/cakes/featured`
* `/cakes/best-sellers`
* `/feedback/recent`

📌 *Customers can only view data; no product modification is allowed.*

---

## 🟢 PHASE 3 – CATEGORY PAGES

(Birthday, Wedding, Cupcakes)

### 🎯 Goal

Display category-based cake listings.

### Tasks

* Birthday cakes page
* Wedding cakes page
* Filtering options:

  * Price
  * Featured status
* Navigation to cake details page

### Backend Interaction

* `/cakes?category=birthday`
* `/cakes?category=wedding`

📌 *Same API endpoints are reused with different filters.*

---

## 🟢 PHASE 4 – CAKE DETAILS & VARIANT SELECTION

(Normal Orders)

### 🎯 Goal

Allow customers to configure predefined cake designs.

### Features

* Cake images and description
* Size selection
* Flavor selection
* Shape selection
* Quantity input
* Special instructions

### Key Logic

* Selected options map to an existing Cake Variant
* Variant price is fetched dynamically
* Variant ID is sent to backend

### Backend Interaction

* `/variants/by-selection`
* `/variants/{id}`

📌 *Customers never calculate prices; pricing is fully controlled by the backend.*

---

## 🟢 PHASE 5 – CART MANAGEMENT

### 🎯 Goal

Allow customers to manage items before checkout.

### Tasks

* Add cake variants to cart
* Update quantities
* Remove items
* View cart summary

### Backend Interaction

* `/cart`
* `/cart/items`

📌 *Cart stores only variant IDs and quantities; prices are always retrieved from variants.*

---

## 🟢 PHASE 6 – CHECKOUT & DELIVERY DETAILS

### 🎯 Goal

Collect delivery and recipient information.

### Checkout Features

* Delivery method:

  * Pickup
  * Delivery
* Delivery date selection
* Address and recipient details
* Delivery instructions
* Approximate distance input (km)

### Business Rules

* Minimum 5 days ahead → allowed
* 2–4 days ahead → loyalty points required
* Less than 2 days → blocked

### Backend Interaction

* `/delivery/validate`
* `/orders/preview`

📌 *Validation is performed on both UI and backend.*

---

## 🟢 PHASE 7 – PAYMENT METHOD SELECTION

(No Payment Gateway)

### 🎯 Goal

Allow customers to select payment method without making immediate payment.

### Payment Options

* Online bank payment (Advance / Full)
* Cash on Delivery (COD)

### Important Rule

❌ No payment is collected during checkout.

### Backend Interaction

* `/orders/create`

📌 Order status → **PLACED / NEW**
📌 Payment status → **UNPAID**

---

## 🟢 PHASE 8 – ORDER PLACEMENT & TRACKING

### 🎯 Goal

Enable customers to track order progress.

### Features

* Order list:

  * All
  * In progress
  * Delivered
  * Cancelled
* Order tracking timeline:

  * Placed
  * Confirmed
  * Preparing
  * Out for delivery
  * Delivered

### Backend Interaction

* `/orders`
* `/orders/{id}`

📌 *Order status updates are controlled only by the admin.*

---

## 🟢 PHASE 9 – PAYMENT AFTER ADMIN CONFIRMATION

### 🎯 Goal

Enable payment only after admin approval.

### Flow

1. Admin confirms order
2. Customer receives notification
3. Customer uploads bank receipt
4. Payment status → **PENDING_VERIFICATION**
5. Admin verifies payment

### Backend Interaction

* `/payments/upload-receipt`
* `/payments/status`

📌 *COD payments are collected at delivery.*

---

## 🟢 PHASE 10 – CUSTOM ORDER FLOW

### 🎯 Goal

Allow customers to place non-standard cake orders.

### Features

* Custom order form:

  * Size
  * Flavor
  * Shape
  * Quantity
  * Special instructions
* No predefined Cake Variant
* Stored as order-specific configuration

### Backend Interaction

* `/custom-orders/create`

📌 *Uses the same checkout, delivery, and payment flow as normal orders.*

---

## 🟢 PHASE 11 – BULK ORDER REQUEST FLOW

### 🎯 Goal

Allow customers to request large or event-based orders.

### Features

* Event name
* Organization
* Event date
* Quantity
* Cake preferences
* Delivery and payment selection

### Backend Interaction

* `/bulk-orders/request`

📌 *Admin approval is required before order creation.*

---

## 🟢 PHASE 12 – LOYALTY POINTS

### 🎯 Goal

Reward repeat customers.

### Loyalty Logic

* Earn: 1 point per Rs.100
* Redeem: 1 point = Rs.1
* Maximum redemption: 10% of order total

### Features

* Display loyalty balance
* Apply points during checkout

### Backend Interaction

* `/loyalty/balance`
* `/loyalty/redeem`

---

## 🟢 PHASE 13 – INVOICES, RATINGS & FEEDBACK

### 🎯 Goal

Enable post-delivery interaction.

### Features

* View invoice
* Submit rating (1–5 stars)
* Submit textual feedback

### Rules

* Ratings allowed only after delivery
* One rating per delivered order item

### Backend Interaction

* `/invoices/{orderId}`
* `/ratings`
* `/feedback`

---

## 🟢 PHASE 14 – MY ACCOUNT & NOTIFICATIONS

### 🎯 Goal

Centralize all customer-related activities.

### My Account Includes

* Dashboard overview
* Profile details
* Wishlist
* Notifications
* Order history

### Backend Interaction

* `/customers/dashboard`
* `/notifications`

---

## 🟢 PHASE 15 – SECURITY, VALIDATION & POLISH

### 🎯 Goal

Ensure system stability, security, and usability.

### Tasks

* Input validation
* Token expiration handling
* Loading and empty states
* User-friendly error messages
* Role-based UI protection

